The paper deals with the problem of drawing graphs and arrangements of pseudolines in the plane, which is a classic topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves combinatorial and algorithmic aspects, such as the NP-completeness and fixed-parameter tractability of certain problems, which are typical of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the topological properties of the drawings, such as homeomorphism and convexity, which are related to graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper mentions the stretchability of the pseudolines, which is a concept from structural informatics (cs.SI).
